Lead.text: 2016-07-06 18:53fileJoffrey, Queen Cersei's sadistic son, ascends the Iron Throne following the death of Robert Baratheon, the Usurper, who won it in battle.
2016-07-06 18:53fileBoth the dour Stannis and the charismatic Renly Baratheon, Robert's brothers, also seek the throne.
2016-07-06 18:53fileRobb Stark, declared King in the North, battles to avenge his father's execution and retrieve his sister from Joffrey's court.
2016-07-06 18:53fileDaenerys, the exiled last heir of the former ruling family, nurtures three dragons and seeks a way home.
2016-07-06 18:53fileLast year when he took ill, the Citadel had sent Pylos out from Oldtown, mere days before Lord Stannis had closed the isle.
2016-07-06 18:53fileHer name was Shireen.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Maester Pylos, do me a kindness and bring the bird down from the rookery for the Lady Shireen ."
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" I had bad dreams,” Shireen told him.
2016-07-06 18:53fileShireen was a summer child, and had never known true cold.
2016-07-06 18:53file"This is the Lady Shireen,” he told the raven.
2016-07-06 18:53fileShireen seemed to grow smaller.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe king — the old king, Aerys II Targaryen, who had not been quite so mad in those days — had sent his lordship to seek a bride for Prince Rhaegar, who had no sisters to wed.
2016-07-06 18:53fileRobert will be delighted with him, and perhaps in time he will even teach Stannis how to laugh ."
2016-07-06 18:53fileNo one had ever taught Stannis how to laugh, least of all the boy Patchface.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Maester, Ser Davos returned last night.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Davos.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>There was a time when Lord Stannis would have woken him, no matter the hour, to have him there to give his counsel.

2016-07-06 18:53fileLord Stannis would be found in the Chamber of the Painted Table, atop the Stone Drum, Dragonstone’s central keep, so named for the way its ancient walls boomed and rumbled during storms.
2016-07-06 18:53fileBut Lord Stannis would not think to come to him, so the maester resigned himself to the ordeal.
2016-07-06 18:53fileHe had stopped to catch his breath and ease the pain in his hip when he heard the scuff of boots on stone, and came face-to-face with Ser Davos Seaworth, descending.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Ser Davos,” the maester said.
2016-07-06 18:53fileIt was said that no one had ever handled a ship by night half so well as Davos Shorthand.
2016-07-06 18:53fileBefore Lord Stannis had knighted him, he had been the most notorious and elusive smuggler in all the Seven Kingdoms.
2016-07-06 18:53fileTo them I’ll always be the Onion Knight ."
2016-07-06 18:53fileHis left hand closed, stubby fingers locking into a fist; Stannis had hacked the ends off at the last joint, all but the thumb.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe others — well, Beric Dondarrion is gone missing, some say dead, and Lord Caron is with Renly.
2016-07-06 18:53fileLoras Tyrell’s their Lord Commander ."
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>It was just the sort of notion that would appeal to Renly Baratheon; a splendid new order of knighthood, with gorgeous new raiment to proclaim it.
2016-07-06 18:53fileEven as a boy, Renly had loved bright colors and rich fabrics, and he had loved his games as well.
2016-07-06 18:53file< emphasis>Oh, Renly, Renly, dear sweet child, do you know what you are doing?
2016-07-06 18:53file< / emphasis > "What reasons did the lords give for their refusals ?" he asked Ser Davos.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Only the false sort, and I’d not do that,” Davos said.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Maester Cressen remembered the day Davos had been knighted, after the siege of Storm’s End.
2016-07-06 18:53fileLord Stannis and a small garrison had held the castle for close to a year, against the great host of the Lords Tyrell and Redwyne.
2016-07-06 18:53fileCloaked in that darkness, Davos the smuggler had dared the Redwyne cordon and the rocks of Shipbreaker Bay alike.
2016-07-06 18:53fileLittle enough, yet it had kept the garrison alive long enough for Eddard Stark to reach Storm’s End and break the siege.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Lord Stannis had rewarded Davos with choice lands on Cape Wrath, a small keep, and a knight’s honors.
2016-07-06 18:53fileDavos had submitted, on the condition that Stannis wield the knife himself; he would accept no punishment from lesser hands.
2016-07-06 18:53fileAfterward, Davos had chosen the name Seaworth for his new-made house, and he took for his banner a black ship on a pale grey field — with an onion on its sails.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe onetime smuggler was fond of saying that Lord Stannis had done him a boon, by giving him four less fingernails to clean and trim.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Ser Davos, truth can be a bitter draught, even for a man like Lord Stannis.
2016-07-06 18:53fileDavos held up his gloved hand.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Lord Stannis Baratheon’s refuge was a great round room with walls of bare black stone and four tall narrow windows that looked out to the four points of the compass.

2016-07-06 18:53fileIn the center of the chamber was the great table from which it took its name, a massive slab of carved wood fashioned at the command of Aegon Targaryen in the days before the Conquest.
2016-07-06 18:53file< emphasis>Hard < / emphasis > was the word men used when they spoke of Stannis, and hard he was.
2016-07-06 18:53fileHis brother, the late King Robert, had grown a beard in his final years.
2016-07-06 18:53fileAs if in answer, Stannis kept his own whiskers cropped tight and short.
2016-07-06 18:53fileSometimes when the world grew very still and silent of a night, Maester Cressen fancied he could hear Lord Stannis grinding his teeth half a castle away.
2016-07-06 18:53fileStannis had never learned to soften his speech, to dissemble or flatter; he said what he thought, and those that did not like it could be damned.
2016-07-06 18:53file"I knew you’d learn what Davos had to say soon enough.
2016-07-06 18:53file"I met Davos on the stair ."
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe bold ones have already declared for Renly.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" < emphasis>His < / emphasis >,” Stannis broke in, "when by rights they should be mine.
2016-07-06 18:53fileI built his fleet and did his work, dutiful as a younger brother should be to an elder, as Renly should be to me.
2016-07-06 18:53fileStorm’s End belonged to House Baratheon for three hundred years; by rights it should have passed to me when Robert took the Iron Throne ."

2016-07-06 18:53fileHere was the heart of his lord’s weakness; for Dragonstone, old and strong though it was, commanded the allegiance of only a handful of lesser lords, whose stony island holdings were too thinly peopled to yield up the men that Stannis needed.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Robert did you an injustice,” Maester Cressen replied carefully, "yet he had sound reasons.
2016-07-06 18:53fileHe needed a man’s strength to rule here, and Renly was but a child ."
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" He is a child still,” Stannis declared, his anger ringing loud in the empty hall, "a thieving child who thinks to snatch the crown off my brow.
2016-07-06 18:53fileWhat has Renly ever done to earn a throne?
2016-07-06 18:53fileHe sits in council and jests with Littlefinger, and at tourneys he dons his splendid suit of armor and allows himself to be knocked off his horse by a better man.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThat is the sum of my brother Renly, who thinks he ought to be a king.
2016-07-06 18:53fileWho maesters for Renly?
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" It would surprise me if Lord Renly sought counsel, Your Grace ."
2016-07-06 18:53fileIn that, as in so much else, Renly was like his brother Robert, and utterly unlike Stannis.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" < emphasis>Your Grace < / emphasis >,” Stannis repeated bitterly.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" I will not treat with Renly,” Stannis answered in a tone that brooked no argument.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Not Renly, then,” the maester yielded.
2016-07-06 18:53fileEddard Stark’s son has been proclaimed King in the North, with all the power of Winterfell and Riverrun behind him ."
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" A green boy,” said Stannis, "and another false king.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Why should I avenge Eddard Stark?
2016-07-06 18:53file< emphasis>I < / emphasis > was his brother, not Ned Stark, but you would never have known it by the way he treated me.
2016-07-06 18:53fileI held Storm’s End for him, watching good men starve while Mace Tyrell and Paxter Redwyne feasted within sight of my walls.
2016-07-06 18:53fileDid Robert thank me?
2016-07-06 18:53file< / emphasis > No, he blamed me for letting Willem Darry steal away Viserys and the babe, as if I could have stopped it.
2016-07-06 18:53fileI sat on his council for fifteen years, helping Jon Arryn rule his realm while Robert drank and whored, but when Jon died, did my brother name me his Hand?
2016-07-06 18:53fileNo, he went galloping off to his dear friend Ned Stark, and offered him the honor.
2016-07-06 18:53fileShe has a young son, Jon Arryn’s heir.
2016-07-06 18:53fileIf you were to betroth Shireen to him —" < / p >
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" The boy is weak and sickly,” Lord Stannis objected.
2016-07-06 18:53fileService as a page might have done him good, but that damnable Lannister woman had Lord Arryn poisoned before it could be done, and now Lysa hides him in the Eyrie.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Then you must send Shireen to the Eyrie,” the maester urged.
2016-07-06 18:53fileStannis furrowed his brow in thought.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Lord Stannis scowled.
2016-07-06 18:53fileLady Selyse was as tall as her husband, thin of body and thin of face, with prominent ears, a sharp nose, and the faintest hint of a mustache on her upper lip.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Lady Arryn owes you her allegiance, as do the Starks, your brother Renly, and all the rest.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Your god can keep his grace,” said Lord Stannis, who did not share his wife’s fervent new faith.
2016-07-06 18:53fileStannis had always been uncomfortable around women, even his own wife.
2016-07-06 18:53fileWhen he had gone to King’s Landing to sit on Robert’s council, he had left Selyse on Dragonstone with their daughter.
2016-07-06 18:53fileIt was said that Stannis knew the strength of every house in the Seven Kingdoms.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe Florent lands lie too close to Highgarden for your lord uncle to risk Mace Tyrell’s wrath ."
2016-07-06 18:53fileLady Selyse moved closer.
2016-07-06 18:53fileYou are meant to sail from this desolate rock as Aegon the Conqueror once sailed, to sweep all before you as he did.
2016-07-06 18:53fileStannis demanded again.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Davos would tell you different,” Stannis said.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Those swords are sworn to Renly.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThey love my charming young brother, as they once loved Robert.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Yes,” she answered, "but if Renly should die.
2016-07-06 18:53fileYour Grace, whatever follies Renly has committed —" < / p >
2016-07-06 18:53fileStannis turned back to his wife.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Melisandre has gazed into the flames, and seen him dead ."
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Lady Selyse gave him a measured look.
2016-07-06 18:53fileHow he might win half a kingdom if he goes to the Starks on his knees and sells our daughter to Lysa Arryn ?"
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" I have heard your counsel, Cressen,” Lord Stannis said.
2016-07-06 18:53fileRobert, Stannis, Renly.
2016-07-06 18:53fileNot the Lady Selyse, the < emphasis>other < / emphasis > one.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Melisandre.
2016-07-06 18:53fileMelisandre of Asshai, sorceress, shadowbinder, and priestess to R’hllor, the Lord of Light, the Heart of Fire, the God of Flame and Shadow.
2016-07-06 18:53fileMelisandre, whose madness must not be allowed to spread beyond Dragonstone.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>And this very night Lord Stannis would feast his bannermen, his lady wife.
2016-07-06 18:53file. and the red woman, Melisandre of Asshai.
2016-07-06 18:53file< / emphasis > He was always summoned for feasts, seated near the salt, close to Lord Stannis.
2016-07-06 18:53fileWhatever he did, Robert had done first, and better.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Maester,” said Lady Melisandre, her deep voice flavored with the music of the Jade Sea.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" A man your age must look to where he steps,” Melisandre said courteously.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Now here is a riddle,” Melisandre said.
2016-07-06 18:53fileMelisandre turned from him in a swirl of red silk and made her way back to the high table, where King Stannis and his queen were seated.
2016-07-06 18:53fileOnly Ser Davos dressed simply, in brown doublet and green wool mantle, and only Ser Davos met his gaze, with pity in his eyes.
2016-07-06 18:53fileYes, loved you, better than Robert even, or Renly, for you were the one unloved, the one who needed me most < / emphasis >< emphasis >.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Ser Davos rose from the bench.
2016-07-06 18:53fileLord Stannis turned away to say something to Melisandre, who had seated herself at his right hand, in the place of high honor.
2016-07-06 18:53fileLady Selyse was on his left, flashing a smile as bright and brittle as her jewels.
2016-07-06 18:53file< emphasis>Too far < / emphasis >, Cressen thought dully, looking at where Ser Davos was seated.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Patchface was capering about as the maester made his slow way around the table to Davos Seaworth.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Ser Davos moved aside to make room on the bench.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe red woman has seen victory in her flames, so Stannis means to press his claim, no matter what the numbers.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Lord Stannis ."
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Stannis turned from the red woman, but it was Lady Selyse who replied.
2016-07-06 18:53file"< emphasis>King < / emphasis > Stannis.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" I make common cause with no one,” Stannis Baratheon said.
2016-07-06 18:53fileLady Selyse took his hand.
2016-07-06 18:53fileIf only he could somehow approach Melisandre unseen.

2016-07-06 18:53file"You are the rightful heir to your brother Robert, the true Lord of the Seven Kingdoms, and King of the Andals, the Rhoynar, and the First Men,” he said desperately, "but even so, you cannot hope to triumph without allies ."
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" He has an ally,” Lady Selyse said.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Yes,” Lady Selyse agreed.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Perhaps he ought sing his counsel henceforth,” Lady Selyse said.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" You go too far, woman,” Lord Stannis said.
2016-07-06 18:53fileDavos saw, but no one else, he was certain.
2016-07-06 18:53fileLady Melisandre, will you share a cup of wine with me?
2016-07-06 18:53fileDavos clutched at him as he left the bench, catching his sleeve with the fingers that Lord Stannis had shortened.
2016-07-06 18:53fileMelisandre of Asshai took the cup from his hands and drank long and deep.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>At Winterfell they had called her "Arya Horseface" and she’d thought nothing could be worse, but that was before the orphan boy Lommy Greenhands had named her "Lumpyhead ."
2016-07-06 18:53fileWhen Yoren had dragged her into that alley she’d thought he meant to kill her, but the sour old man had only held her tight, sawing through her mats and tangles with his dagger.
2016-07-06 18:53file"I’m taking men and boys from the city,” Yoren growled as the sharp steel scraped at her head.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Lord Eddard gave me pick o" the dungeons, and I didn’t find no little lordlings down there.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe Lannister guardsmen on the gate were stopping everyone, but Yoren called one by name and their wagons were waved through.
2016-07-06 18:53fileNo one spared Arya a glance.
2016-07-06 18:53fileArya never looked back.

2016-07-06 18:53fileShe wished the Rush would rise and wash the whole city away, Flea Bottom and the Red Keep and the Great Sept and < emphasis>everything < / emphasis >, and every<emphasis>one < / emphasis > too, especially Prince Joffrey and his mother.
2016-07-06 18:53fileBut she knew it wouldn’t, and anyhow Sansa was still in the city and would wash away too.
2016-07-06 18:53fileWhen she remembered that, Arya decided to wish for Winterfell instead.
2016-07-06 18:53fileYoren had plucked some from the streets with promises of food for their bellies and shoes for their feet.
2016-07-06 18:53fileTeams of plow horses pulled the wagons, and Yoren had bought two coursers and a half-dozen donkeys for the boys.
2016-07-06 18:53fileArya would have preferred a real horse, but the donkey was better than riding on a wagon.
2016-07-06 18:53fileJon Snow had given her Needle.
2016-07-06 18:53fileMaybe she had to let them call her Lumpyhead, but she wasn’t going to let them call Jon a thief.
2016-07-06 18:53file< emphasis>Yes I do < / emphasis >, Arya could have said.
2016-07-06 18:53fileYoren didn’t know about the stableboy, but she was afraid of what he might do if he found out.

2016-07-06 18:53fileArya was pretty sure that some of the other men were killers too, the three in the manacles for sure, but the queen wasn’t looking for < emphasis>them < / emphasis >, so it wasn’t the same.
2016-07-06 18:53fileWhen Hot Pie began to wail, Arya whirled toward Lommy Greenhands, who was sitting on his donkey openmouthed.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>The Bull shouted, "Behind you,” and Arya spun.
2016-07-06 18:53fileArya slid into a water dancer’s stance and waited.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>By the time Yoren pulled her off him, Hot Pie was sprawled out on the ground with his breeches brown and smelly, crying as Arya whapped him over and over and over.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe fat one snapped his pointy teeth together and hissed, but Arya ignored him.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Sullenly, Arya did as he said.
2016-07-06 18:53file< emphasis>I won’t < / emphasis >, Arya thought stubbornly, but when Yoren laid the wood against the back of her bare thighs, the shriek burst out of her anyway.
2016-07-06 18:53fileArya shrieked again, clutching the tree to keep from falling.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Might be I got your attention now,” Yoren said.
2016-07-06 18:53file< emphasis>They" re not my brothers < / emphasis >, Arya thought as she bent to yank up her breeches, but she knew better than to say so.
2016-07-06 18:53file< emphasis>Calm as still water < / emphasis >, she told herself, the way Syrio Forel had taught her.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" I know,” Arya muttered sullenly.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" < emphasis>Joffrey < / emphasis >,” Arya breathed.
2016-07-06 18:53fileYoren tossed back her stick sword.
2016-07-06 18:53fileHot Pie was worse off; Yoren had to shift some barrels around so he could lie in the back of a wagon on some sacks of barley, and he whimpered every time the wheels hit a rock.
2016-07-06 18:53fileLommy Greenhands wasn’t even hurt, yet he stayed as far away from Arya as he could get.

2016-07-06 18:53fileWhen Arya squinted the right way she could see the sword too, only it wasn’t a new sword, it was Ice, her father’s greatsword, all ripply Valyrian steel, and the red was Lord Eddard’s blood on the blade after Ser Ilyn the King’s Justice had cut off his head.
2016-07-06 18:53fileYoren had made her look away when it happened, yet it seemed to her that the comet looked like Ice must have, after.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe kingsroad wound its way past Winterfell on its way to the Wall, and Yoren had promised he’d leave her there with no one any wiser about who she’d been.
2016-07-06 18:53fileShe yearned to see her mother again, and Robb and Bran and Rickon.
2016-07-06 18:53file. but it was Jon Snow she thought of most.
2016-07-06 18:53fileShe wished somehow they could come to the Wall before Winterfell, so Jon might muss up her hair and call her "little sister ."
2016-07-06 18:53fileSansa was watching it from her tower window when Ser Arys Oakheart arrived to escort her down to the tourney grounds.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Glory to your betrothed,” Ser Arys answered at once.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Doubtless that was what they told Joffrey; Sansa was not so sure.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" King Joffrey sits where Aegon the Dragon once sat, in the castle built by his son,” Ser Arys said.
2016-07-06 18:53file< / emphasis > Her mother was one of Joffrey’s enemies now, her brother Robb another.
2016-07-06 18:53fileMust Robb and her lady mother die next?
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe comet was red, but Joffrey was Baratheon as much as Lannister, and their sigil was a black stag on a golden field.
2016-07-06 18:53file"You look very lovely today, my lady,” Ser Arys said.
2016-07-06 18:53fileKnowing that Joffrey would require her to attend the tourney in his honor, Sansa had taken special care with her face and clothes.
2016-07-06 18:53fileShe wore a gown of pale purple silk and a moonstone hair net that had been a gift from Joffrey.
2016-07-06 18:53fileWhen they told him that Robb had been proclaimed King in the North, his rage had been a fearsome thing, and he had sent Ser Boros to beat her.
2016-07-06 18:53fileSer Arys offered his arm and she let him lead her from her chamber.
2016-07-06 18:53fileIf she must have one of the Kingsguard dogging her steps, Sansa preferred that it be him.
2016-07-06 18:53fileArys Oakheart was courteous, and would talk to her cordially.
2016-07-06 18:53fileOnce he even objected when Joffrey commanded him to hit her.
2016-07-06 18:53file. except for the Hound, but Joff never asked the Hound to punish her.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Ser Arys had light-brown hair and a face that was not unpleasant to look upon.
2016-07-06 18:53fileSansa asked as they descended the steps arm in arm.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" I will,” Ser Arys answered, smiling.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>The last tourney had been different, Sansa reflected.
2016-07-06 18:53fileKing Robert had staged it in her father’s honor.
2016-07-06 18:53fileRobert Baratheon was dead, and her father as well, beheaded for a traitor on the steps of the Great Sept of Baelor.
2016-07-06 18:53fileSansa always felt safer when Cersei was there to restrain her son.
2016-07-06 18:53fileSer Arys dropped his voice.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Lord Tywin has gone to ground at Harrenhal instead of bringing his army to the city as the queen commanded.
2016-07-06 18:53fileSer Arys was fond of gossip, but only when he was certain that no one was listening.
2016-07-06 18:53filePrincess Myrcella and Prince Tommen sat behind him.
2016-07-06 18:53fileIn the back of the royal box, Sandor Clegane stood at guard, his hands resting on his swordbelt.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Lady Sansa,” the Hound announced curtly when he saw her.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Princess Myrcella nodded a shy greeting at the sound of Sansa’s name, but plump little Prince Tommen jumped up eagerly.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Sansa, did you hear?
2016-07-06 18:53fileTommen was all of eight.
2016-07-06 18:53fileHe reminded her of her own little brother, Bran.
2016-07-06 18:53fileBran was back at Winterfell, a cripple, yet safe.
2016-07-06 18:53file"I fear for the life of your foeman,” she told Tommen solemnly.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Ser Arys bowed.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p>Joffrey waved a curt dismissal while he studied Sansa from head to heels.
2016-07-06 18:53fileSansa was relieved.
2016-07-06 18:53fileFor a moment Sansa was afraid he meant Robb.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Viserys.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe last son of Mad King Aerys.
2016-07-06 18:53file< / emphasis > Sansa kept her tone cool and polite, yet even so Joffrey’s eyes narrowed as he tried to decide whether she was mocking him.
2016-07-06 18:53file< emphasis>He < / emphasis > had been the champion in her father’s tourney, Sansa remembered.
2016-07-06 18:53fileJoffrey was fond of making men fight to the death.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe Hound had never taken a knight’s vows.
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe Redwyne twins were the queen’s unwilling guests, even as Sansa was.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" Poorly ridden,” declared King Joffrey.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" < emphasis>Ser Balon Swann, of Stonehelm in the Red Watch < / emphasis >,” came the herald’s cry.
2016-07-06 18:53file"< emphasis>Morros of House Slynt, heir to Lord Janos of Harrenhal < / emphasis > ."
2016-07-06 18:53fileThe lance was a knight’s weapon, Sansa knew, the Slynts lowborn.
2016-07-06 18:53fileLord Janos had been no more than commander of the City Watch before Joffrey had raised him to Harrenhal and the council.
2016-07-06 18:53file< emphasis>I hope Ser Balon kills him < / emphasis >< emphasis >.

2016-07-06 18:53file< / emphasis > When Joffrey proclaimed her father’s death, it had been Janos Slynt who seized Lord Eddard’s severed head by the hair and raised it on high for king and crowd to behold, while Sansa wept and screamed.
2016-07-06 18:53fileSansa was appalled, wondering if the gods had heard her vengeful prayer.
2016-07-06 18:53file"Tommen, we picked the wrong foe for you,” the king told his brother.
2016-07-06 18:53fileJoffrey curled his lip.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" I warned you,” said the Hound.
2016-07-06 18:53fileIt made Sansa anxious.
2016-07-06 18:53fileWhen Joffrey Baratheon’s mood darkened, any chance word might set off one of his rages.
2016-07-06 18:53file< p >" < emphasis>Lothor Brune, freerider in the service of Lord Baelish < / emphasis >,” cried the herald.
